criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Men more than 18 years old with clinical suspicion of prostate cancer;

          2. Serum PSA ≤ 20 ng/ml within the previous 3 months;

          3. Suspected stage ≤ T2 on rectal examination (organ-confined prostate cancer) within the
             previous 3 months;

          4. No evidence of PSA increase by noncancerous factors, such as catheterization, bladder
             stones, or urinary tract infection including bacterial prostatitis;

          5. mpMRI PI-RADS V2 score 4 or 5；

          6. Able to provide written informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Prior prostate biopsy or prostate surgery;

          2. Prior treatment for prostate cancer;

          3. Contraindication to MRI (e.g. claustrophobia, pacemaker, estimated glomerular
             filtration rate ≤ 50mls/min);

          4. Contraindication to prostate biopsy.
